            In today’s interconnected world, human translation services play a
            vital role in breaking language barriers and ensuring effective
            communication across cultures. While machine translation has gained
            popularity for its speed, it often falls short in capturing the
            nuances and context of human languages. This article explores the
            benefits of specialized human translation, its costs, and why it
            remains indispensable for businesses and their corporate and
            business documents.
        </p>

        <h2 id="what-are-human-translation-services">
            What Are Human Translation Services?
        </h2>

        <p>
            Human translation services involve professional linguists, who
            translate written or spoken content between languages. These experts
            combine their knowledge of grammar, culture, industry and context to
            ensure translations are both accurate and meaningful. Unlike machine
            translation, which often produces literal or robotic results, human
            translators ensure your message is fully understood by the target
            audience.
        </p>
        <p>Common Use Cases for Human Translation Services:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Legal documents (contracts, patents)</li>
            <li>
                <a href="/posts/financial-translation-services"
                    >Financial and accounting documents</a
                >
            </li>
            <li>Business communication (corporate reports, proposals)</li>
            <li>
                <a href="/posts/marketing-translation-services"
                    >Marketing materials</a
                > (campaigns, slogans, advertisements)
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="/posts/russian-localization"
                    >Web and app localization</a
                >
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="why-choose-human-translation-over-machine-translation">
            Why Choose Human Translation Over Machine Translation?
        </h2>

        <strong><p>Accuracy and Context</p></strong>
        <p>
            Human translators understand the nuances of language and ensure that
            each word and phrase is translated correctly in its specific
            context. For example, idioms or culturally unique phrases often
            require creative adaptation, which machine translation cannot
            achieve.
        </p>
        <strong><p>Cultural Sensitivity</p></strong>
        <p>
            A professional human translator makes sure that your content aligns
            with the cultural norms and expectations of the target audience.
            This is particularly important in marketing and advertising, where
            the wrong message could harm your brand.
        </p>
        <strong><p>Consistency in Specialized Terminology</p></strong>
        <p>
            Fields like law and finance require precise terminology. Human
            translation services ensure consistency and accuracy in such
            critical areas, which is why they are preferred for high-stakes
            documents. For the sake of clarity, a human translator cannot know
            everything. Legal and financial documents cannot and must not be
            translated by just any human translator. They <strong
                >must only be entrusted to human translators, who specialize in
                law and finance</strong
            >
            respectively. Keep this important detail in mind next time you go searching
            for translation services.
        </p>

        <h2 id="understanding-human-translation-costs">
            Understanding Human Translation Costs
        </h2>

        <p>One common question is: What does human translation cost?</p>
        <p>The cost of human translation depends on several factors:</p>

        <ol>
            <li>Language Pair: Rare language combinations often cost more.</li>
            <li>
                Complexity of the Content: financial, marketing, or legal
                translations typically cost more than general content.
                SEO-driven content adds to the cost, as it requires in-depth
                keyword research in addition to the
                translation-editing-proofreading (TEP).
            </li>
            <li>
                Urgency: Rush projects may include additional rush fees
                (typically a 20-30% surcharge).
            </li>
            <li>Volume: Larger projects may qualify for bulk discounts.</li>
        </ol>

        <p>Average Cost of Human Translation Services:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Per Word: Typically ranges from $0.06 for simple, everyday texts
                with straightforward language to $0.20 per word for more complex
                content that requires not only translation but also SEO.
                However, the realistic current market price for professional
                translation of specialized texts without SEO hovers around
                $0.10-$0.12 per source word. Not everyone needs SEO.
            </li>
            <li>
                Per Hour: For specialized tasks like editing or proofreading,
                the hourly rate may range from $20 to $50.
            </li>
            <li>
                Flat Project Fees: Some projects, like website localization or
                document bundles, may be priced as a package.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            While machine translation may appear cheaper upfront, the additional
            time and cost needed for human editing often negate the savings.
            Investing in human translation ensures quality from the start.
        </p>
